The paper deals with a mechanism design problem in which voters submit proposals for how to allocate a divisible resource among several alternatives. This falls under the category of computational social choice (cs.GT) and algorithmic game theory (cs.EC). The paper also introduces a new mechanism, which involves market prices, and discusses its properties, which could fall under the category of distributed systems (cs.DS) or social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the tradeoff between Pareto optimality and proportionality, which could fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
